      "title": "In Photos: Women’s March Takes on Los Angeles",
      "category": "Multimedia",
      "subcategory": "Photo",
      "publish_date": "2017-01-24T08:00:00.000Z",
      "full_thumbnail": "https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1",
      "mobile_thumbnail": "https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=980%2C647&ssl=1",
      "description": "Laverne Cox, Miley Cyrus, and Barbara Streisand were a few of the many celebrities who made speeches, though the intense crows made it impossible for most to see or hear. These protests were held on e...",
      "content": "<div class="single-post-content">
            <p>Over 750,000 protesters gathered in Los Angeles on Saturday in support of the Women’s March on Washington. Marchers gathered in Pershing Square downtown, and held signs promoting women’s rights, protection of the environment and racial equality, among others.</p>
<p>Laverne Cox, Miley Cyrus, and Barbara Streisand were a few of the many celebrities who made speeches, though the intense crowds made it impossible for most to see or hear. These protests were held on every continent, and many had record-breaking turnouts.</p>
<div id="attachment_75110" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg" data-slb-active="1" data-slb-asset="1842772837" data-slb-internal="0" data-slb-group="75166"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-75110" data-attachment-id="75110" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2017-01-24/women-take-los-angeles-marching/img_4453/" data-orig-file="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?fit=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2048,1365" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="Womens March Watchers" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?fit=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?fit=888%2C592&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-75110" src="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=800%2C533" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4453.jpg?w=1776 1776w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-recalc-dims="1"></a><p id="caption-attachment-75110" class="wp-caption-text">Protesters take a break on top of an ATM sign to watch marchers go by. <em>Tamari Dzotsenidze / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>
<div id="attachment_75109" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg" data-slb-active="1" data-slb-asset="2061846597" data-slb-internal="0" data-slb-group="75166"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-75109" data-attachment-id="75109" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2017-01-24/women-take-los-angeles-marching/img_4491/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?fit=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2048,1365" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="Womens March Signs" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?fit=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?fit=888%2C592&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-75109" src="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?resize=800%2C533" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?resize=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4491.jpg?w=1776 1776w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-recalc-dims="1"></a><p id="caption-attachment-75109" class="wp-caption-text">Women hold up signs in solidarity. <em>Tamari Dzotsenidze / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>
<div id="attachment_75106" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-75106" data-attachment-id="75106" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2017-01-24/women-take-los-angeles-marching/img_4521/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?fit=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2048,1365" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="Womens March- Tampons" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?fit=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?fit=888%2C592&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-75106" src="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?resize=800%2C533" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?resize=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4521.jpg?w=1776 1776w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-recalc-dims="1"><p id="caption-attachment-75106" class="wp-caption-text">Janelle Obert, Mennelle Alkhawaja and Clare Taylor Wilkes from the band No Girlfriends dressed as tampons as a “matter of protecting planned parenthood.” <em>Tamari Dzotsenidze / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>
<div id="attachment_75107" style="width: 810px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg" data-slb-active="1" data-slb-asset="784010377" data-slb-internal="0" data-slb-group="75166"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-75107" data-attachment-id="75107" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2017-01-24/women-take-los-angeles-marching/img_4518/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?fit=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2048,1365" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="Womens March- Tampons 2" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?fit=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?fit=888%2C592&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-75107" src="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?resize=800%2C533" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?resize=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/IMG_4518.jpg?w=1776 1776w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" data-recalc-dims="1"></a><p id="caption-attachment-75107" class="wp-caption-text">“I also wanted to make a statement because so many people in the GOP tell us what to do with our vaginas, and yet so many people don’t know anything about them. We’re kind of like this is what our vaginas do.” <em>Tamari Dzotsenidze / Daily Nexus</em></p></div>
