      "content": "<div class="single-post-content">
            <p>On Wednesday, two of the University of California’s unions – American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees 3299 and the University Professional and Technical Employees – held a one-day strike. The unions have been negotiating new contracts with the UC since 2017; both parties have yet to come to an agreement.</p>
<p>This was the third strike from union workers that the UC has seen within the past year.</p>
<p>Check out photos of the strike captured by <em>Nexus</em> photographers below:</p><!--Ad Injection:random--><script type="text/javascript"> 

