      "content": "<div class="single-post-content">
            <div id="attachment_85262" style="width: 910px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg" data-slb-active="1" data-slb-asset="1342522946" data-slb-internal="0" data-slb-group="89699"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-85262" data-attachment-id="85262" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2018-12-07/as-showcase-comes-home-gauchos-left-wondering-what-could-have-been/msoccer-vscalpoly-oct2718-angiebanks-21/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?fit=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2048,1365" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?fit=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?fit=888%2C592&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-85262" src="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?resize=888%2C592" alt="" width="888" height="592" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?w=2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?resize=250%2C167&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/MSoccer-vsCalPoly-Oct2718-AngieBanks-21.jpg?w=1776 1776w" sizes="(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px" data-recalc-dims="1"></a><p id="caption-attachment-85262" class="wp-caption-text">Angie Banks/Daily Nexus</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The UCSB men’s soccer team had a roller coaster of a weekend as they outlasted the UNLV Rebels for their first win of the year on Friday night, and only 48 hours later took their first loss of the season against the No.16 Virginia Tech Hokies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Gauchos are now 1-1 on the season, the Rebels sit at 0-1 and the Hokies end their West Coast road trip at 2-0.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Friday night matchup against UNLV was a battle of attrition for the Gauchos, and although they ended up with the 2-1 win in double overtime, they suffered some big injuries that will certainly impact the team these next couple weeks.</span></p><!--Ad Injection:random--><script type="text/javascript"> 

