      "title": "Max Heidegger Leads Gauchos to Solid Win Over CSUN",
      "category": "Sports",
      "subcategory": "Basketball",
      "publish_date": "2019-02-07T08:00:00.000Z",
      "full_thumbnail": "https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1",
      "mobile_thumbnail": "https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?resize=980%2C647&ssl=1",
      "description": "Max Heidegger had his first signature performance of the year, as his 26 points guided the Gauchos to a 70-64 victory over the Matadors.",
      "content": "<div class="single-post-content">
            <div id="attachment_80674" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg" data-slb-active="1" data-slb-asset="609247814" data-slb-internal="0" data-slb-group="86056"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-80674" data-attachment-id="80674" data-permalink="https://dailynexus.com/2018-02-01/protect-the-dome-gauchos-host-hawaii-aiming-to-seize-control-of-big-west/mbball_atusc-171217-dustinharris-06-web-2/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?fit=1365%2C2048&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1365,2048" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta='{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0"}' data-image-title="MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?fit=167%2C250&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?fit=683%2C1024&amp;ssl=1" class="wp-image-80674" src="https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1-683x1024.jpg?resize=600%2C900" alt="" width="600" height="900" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?resize=683%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 683w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?resize=167%2C250&amp;ssl=1 167w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?resize=768%2C1152&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/MBball_atUSC-171217-DustinHarris-06-web-1.jpg?w=1365&amp;ssl=1 1365w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1"></a><p id="caption-attachment-80674" class="wp-caption-text">Max Heidegger reaches past the defense toward the hoop. Dustin Harris/Daily Nexus</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Behind a huge 26-point performance by star junior guard Max Heidegger, the UCSB men’s basketball team took down the CSUN Matadors 70-64. With the win, UCSB rose to a 6-2 conference, 17-5 overall record and solidified its second place standing in the Big West. The Matadors dropped to a 4-4 conference, 10-14 overall record on the year and stayed put at fifth place in the conference standing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Gauchos actually struggled out of the gate, turning the ball over on three of their first four possessions. In total, UCSB had 11 turnovers in the first half, leading to 12 points for CSUN.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">“We had a slow start, which is unacceptable,” freshman forward Amadou Sow pointed out postgame. “We came out slow, and let them do whatever they wanted to do.”</span></p><!--Ad Injection:random--><script type="text/javascript"> 

