            <p>I grew up thinking coffee was the forbidden fruit.</p>
<p>After nearly two decades of believing coffee could stunt my growth, science has shown that my mom was wrong all along. “What I tell patients is, if you like coffee,” Dr. Peter Martin, the director of the Institute for Coffee Studies at Vanderbilt University, says, “go ahead and drink as much as you want and can.”</p>
